it it a tool for automation purpose
before installation of maven we need to install java 
yum install java-1.8.0-openjdk-devel
java --version
wget maven binary code
from maven downloads
u get apache.tar.zip file
u need to zip it using
tar -zxuv
now u get apache file
cd apache
cd bin
there u will find mvn --version
but now u need see maven at anywhere so go to root
sudo su
open bash profile
vi prompt opens
PATH=$PATH:$M3-user@
now u find maven outside bin also
apart from maven
